The local community government and response personnel would then initiate the proper response warranted by the situation. This system provides a means of facilitating quick response to an incident, as well as notifying the public of an incident if necessary. In addition to periodic LEPC meetings, Superior Refining Company conducts periodic emergency response exercises that involve refinery personnel, contractors, and emergency response organizations. The Refinery provides annual refresher training to on-site emergency responders regarding their responsibilities during an emergency and also has a trained emergency response team.

PLANNED CHANGES TO IMPROVE SAFETY
Superior Refining Company is in the process of rebuilding the Refinery and has taken numerous steps to enhance process safety.  Such steps include, but are not limited to, the following:

* Conduct new process hazard analyses for each Refinery unit;
* Rewrite the unit operating procedures in a new usability mapping format;
* Upgrade the materials of construction of certain piping and vessels;
* Enhance leak detection by adding new hydrocarbon and hydrofluoric acid release detectors and cameras;
* Install a Rapid Acid Transfer System in the HF Alkylation Unit;
* Install and upgrade fire monitors;
* Conduct intensive operator training with use of a training simulator;
